# Code & Implementation

## Server Actions
- Use for: data-mutating form submits (create/update/delete), server-side validation + DB access, mutations not tied to an RTK Query cache. Use RTK Query mutations instead for optimistic updates, `invalidatesTags`, or when fired from a Client Component already using RTK Query.
- `'use server'` in `src/actions/*` or inline in an RSC; never in a file that also has `'use client'` components.
- Validate input with Zod first; use only parsed data — never trust raw `formData`.
- Return a typed `{ success, error?, data? }` — never throw (Client needs the error state); never return raw errors/stack traces/secrets.
- Revalidate after success via `revalidatePath`/`revalidateTag`. Consume with `useActionState` (React 19) + `useFormStatus` for pending state.
- Don't use Server Actions for GET (use `fetch()` in RSC). Don't skip Zod even for simple fields.

## Route Handlers
- `src/app/api/[resource]/route.ts`, named exports per HTTP method (`GET`/`POST`/`PATCH`/`DELETE`); dynamic `params` is a Promise — await it.
- Validate body with Zod (422 + `error.flatten()` on failure). Extract + validate Bearer token on every protected endpoint (401 if missing).
- No business logic / DB access here — call the external API or a service fn. Never leak stack traces, DB errors, or internal paths.
- Use `NextRequest`/`NextResponse`. Status map: 200 ok · 201 created · 204 no content · 400 bad · 401 unauth · 403 forbidden · 404 not found · 422 validation · 500 server.

## Forms (react-hook-form + Zod + MUI)
- `useForm` + `zodResolver`; derive `FormValues` via `z.infer`. Schema in the component file unless shared → `src/types/`.
- Wrap MUI inputs in `Controller` (never `register()`); use `register()` only for native inputs. Set `noValidate` (rely on RHF+Zod, not HTML5).
- Field errors via `helperText` (TextField) / `FormHelperText` (Select). Disable submit while loading + reflect in label. Reset form and uncontrolled refs (file inputs via `useRef`) after success.
- Show API errors separately from field errors, extracting the message string. Progressive-enhancement forms use `useActionState` + a Server Action.
- Don't manage form values with `useState`. Don't call mutations from `useEffect` — only `onSubmit`. Don't render raw API error objects.

## SCSS Modules
- Abstracts are auto-injected (`next.config.ts` → `sassOptions.additionalData`). Never add `@use 'abstracts' as *;` — vars + mixins are already available.
- Vars (`_variables.scss`): `$color-*` (`primary`/`error`/`success`/`white`/`gray-50…900`), `$space-1…16`, `$font-size-xs…3xl`, `$font-weight-normal…bold`, `$radius-sm…full`, `$shadow-sm…lg`, `$bp-sm…2xl`, `$z-dropdown/sticky/modal/toast`, `$transition-fast…slow`.
- Mixins (`_mixins.scss`): `respond-to(sm|md|lg|xl|2xl)`, `flex-center`, `flex-between`, `flex-col-gap($gap)`, `truncate`, `line-clamp($n)`, `sr-only`, `focus-ring($color?)`, `card($padding?)`.
- Co-locate `.module.scss` with its component. kebab-case files + classes; semantic names (`wrapper`/`header`/`field`/`error`), not visual (`red-text`). BEM nesting with `&` (`&--mod`, `&__el`).
- `src/app/globals.css` is Tailwind-only (PostCSS) — no SCSS syntax. Style MUI with `sx`/theme (incl. spacing/layout overrides); SCSS for page shells, wrappers, and non-MUI UI — never put a visual SCSS class on a MUI root.
